NAME
       yes - output a string repeatedly until killed

SYNOPSIS
       yes [STRING]...
       yes OPTION

DESCRIPTION
       Repeatedly output a line with all specified STRING(s), or 'y'.

OPTIONS
       --help display this help and exit

       --version
              output version information and exit

NOTES
       yes uses an 8192-byte write buffer for efficient output.
       Multiple STRING arguments are joined with spaces.

EXIT STATUS
       Always runs until killed or a write error occurs.

AUTHORS
       LikeOS-64 project.

SEE ALSO
       true(1), sh(1)

